)
static

Try to build a bitmap atlas.

This involves examining a sequence of display lists which contain glBitmap commands and putting the bitmap images into a texture map (the atlas). If we succeed, gl_bitmap_atlas::complete will be set to true. If we fail, gl_bitmap_atlas::incomplete will be set to true.

§ unpack_image()

static GLvoid* unpack_image ( struct gl_context *  ctx,
GLuint  dimensions,
GLsizei  width,
GLsizei  height,
GLsizei  depth,
GLenum  format,
GLenum  type,
const GLvoid *  pixels,
const struct gl_pixelstore_attrib *  unpack 
)
static

Wrapper for _mesa_unpack_image/bitmap() that handles pixel buffer objects.

If width < 0 or height < 0 or format or type are invalid we'll just return NULL. We will not generate an error since OpenGL command arguments aren't error-checked until the command is actually executed (not when they're compiled). But if we run out of memory, GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY will be recorded.

References _mesa_bytes_per_pixel(), _mesa_error(), _mesa_is_bufferobj(), _mesa_unpack_image(), _mesa_validate_pbo_access(), ADD_POINTERS, gl_pixelstore_attrib::BufferObj, gl_context::Driver, MAP_INTERNAL, dd_function_table::MapBufferRange, gl_buffer_object::Size, and dd_function_table::UnmapBuffer.
